  "prompt": "How do I focus for the final CA exam?",
  "response": "Here are some tips to help you focus and prepare for the final CA exam:\n\n1. Study Planning\n- Create a structured study schedule\n- Prioritize topics based on weightage and difficulty\n- Allocate sufficient time for each subject\n- Include mock tests and revision\n\n2. Study Techniques\n- Use active learning methods\n- Take concise notes\n- Practice solving multiple question papers\n- Focus on understanding concepts, not just memorizing\n- Use mind maps and flowcharts\n\n3. Time Management\n- Follow a consistent daily routine\n- Set specific study hours\n- Take short, planned breaks\n- Use time management techniques like Pomodoro\n- Avoid distractions\n\n4. Physical and Mental Preparation\n- Maintain a healthy diet\n- Exercise regularly\n- Get adequate sleep\n- Practice meditation/stress management\n- Stay motivated and positive\n\n5. Resources\n- Use standard study materials\n- Join coaching classes/online tutorials\n- Solve previous years' question papers\n- Participate in study groups\n- Use online practice platforms\n\n6. Last-Minute Tips\n- Focus on revision\n- Practice time management during exam\n- Stay calm and confident\n- Get proper sleep before exam\n- Carry necessary stationery\n\n7. Additional Support\n- Seek guidance from mentors\n- Discuss challenging topics with peers\n- Stay connected with supportive family/friends",
